&lt;Kobe Steel Ltd> said it has agreed tosupply technology to manufacture thin-walled copper tubing usedin air conditioners and refrigeration units to &lt;HalsteadIndustries Inc> in Zelienople, Pennsylvania.    Total demand for copper tubing in the U.S. Is 25,000 tonnesa month, of which 5,000 is for the thin-walled type, Kobe saidin a statement.    The two companies are studying joint partial production ofKobe's thin-walled copper tubing in the U.S. REUTER&#3;